### [High] Missing Access Control on checkList Allows Anyone to Manipulate the Naughty/Nice List

**Affected Files:** src/SantasList.sol

**Description**

SantasList maintains a mapping of addresses to their Status (NAUGHTY, NICE, EXTRA_NICE). Only Santa should be able to call checkList to assign statuses. The checkList function has no access control modifier — any address can call it to set any target address to any status.

```solidity
// src/SantasList.sol
@> function checkList(address person, Status status) external {
   // @> Missing: require(msg.sender == i_santa, "Only Santa can check the list");
       s_theList[person] = status;
   }
```

**Risk**

- Any EOA or contract can call checkList at any time with no preconditions.
- A griefing actor can deny NICE status by calling `checkList(victim, Status.NAUGHTY)` before Santa's check-in.

**Impact**

- Legitimate NICE users are blocked from collecting presents.
- Attackers can set themselves to EXTRA_NICE to gain the highest reward tier.

**Proof of Concept**

```solidity
function test_AnyoneCanCallCheckList() public {
    address attacker = makeAddr("attacker");
    address victim = makeAddr("victim");

    vm.prank(santa);
    santasList.checkList(victim, SantasList.Status.NICE);
    assertEq(uint256(santasList.s_theList(victim)), uint256(SantasList.Status.NICE));

    vm.prank(attacker);
    santasList.checkList(victim, SantasList.Status.NAUGHTY);
    assertEq(uint256(santasList.s_theList(victim)), uint256(SantasList.Status.NAUGHTY));

    vm.warp(santasList.CHRISTMAS_2023_BLOCK_TIME() + 1);
    vm.prank(victim);
    vm.expectRevert();
    santasList.collectPresent();
}
```

**Recommended Mitigation**

```diff
- function checkList(address person, Status status) external {
+ function checkList(address person, Status status) external onlySanta {
      s_theList[person] = status;
  }
```

