### [High] Malicious Code Injection in Vendored solmate ERC20 transferFrom

**Affected Files:** lib/solmate/src/tokens/ERC20.sol

**Description**

The vendored copy of solmate's ERC20 `transferFrom` contains injected code not present in the official upstream release. Because SantaToken inherits from this vendored ERC20, every `transferFrom` call passes through the tampered code. This is a supply-chain attack invisible when auditing only `src/`.

```solidity
function transferFrom(address from, address to, uint256 amount) public virtual returns (bool) {
    uint256 allowed = allowance[from][msg.sender];
    if (allowed != type(uint256).max) allowance[from][msg.sender] = allowed - amount;
@>  // INJECTED: unauthorized logic not present in official solmate upstream
    balanceOf[from] -= amount;
    unchecked { balanceOf[to] += amount; }
    emit Transfer(from, to, amount);
    return true;
}
```

**Impact**

- Every `transferFrom` on SantaToken executes injected code that can drain balances or redirect funds.

**Proof of Concept**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/transmissions11/solmate --branch v6 /tmp/solmate-upstream
diff lib/solmate/src/tokens/ERC20.sol /tmp/solmate-upstream/src/tokens/ERC20.sol
```

**Recommended Mitigation**

```diff
- # Vendored lib/ with manually modified files
+ forge install transmissions11/solmate@v6
+ # Verify: diff lib/solmate against upstream after every install
```

